# [Account Management (AC-2)](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/governance/policy/samples/nist-sp-800-53-r4#account-management) 

	a.‚ÄÉDefine and document the types of accounts allowed and specifically prohibited for use within the system;
	b.‚ÄÉAssign account managers;
	c.‚ÄÉRequire [Assignment: organization-defined prerequisites and criteria] for group and role membership;
	d.‚ÄÉSpecify:
		1.‚ÄÉAuthorized users of the system;
		2.‚ÄÉGroup and role membership; and
		3.‚ÄÉAccess authorizations (i.e., privileges) and [Assignment: organization-defined attributes (as required)] for each account;
	e.‚ÄÉRequire approvals by [Assignment: organization-defined personnel or roles] for requests to create accounts;
	f.‚ÄÉCreate, enable, modify, disable, and remove accounts in accordance with [Assignment: organization-defined policy, procedures, prerequisites, and criteria];
	g.‚ÄÉMonitor the use of accounts;
	h.‚ÄÉNotify account managers and [Assignment: organization-defined personnel or roles] within:
		1.‚ÄÉ[Assignment: organization-defined time period] when accounts are no longer required;
		2.‚ÄÉ[Assignment: organization-defined time period] when users are terminated or transferred; and
		3.‚ÄÉ[Assignment: organization-defined time period] when system usage or need-to-know changes for an individual;
	i.‚ÄÉAuthorize access to the system based on:
		1.‚ÄÉA valid access authorization;
		2.‚ÄÉIntended system usage; and
		3.‚ÄÉ[Assignment: organization-defined attributes (as required)];
	j.‚ÄÉReview accounts for compliance with account management requirements [Assignment: organization-defined frequency];
	k.‚ÄÉEstablish and implement a process for changing shared or group account authenticators (if deployed) when individuals are removed from the group; and
	l.‚ÄÉAlign account management processes with personnel termination and transfer processes.

